THE parents of slain top rapper Kiernan “AKA” Forbes (35) have appealed to Mzansi for some space and time to mourn. AKA and his close friend, aged 34, were shot dead on their way out of Wish restaurant on Florida road in Durban on Friday night, 10 February. It is believed that the two were there for refreshments before his performance for a party called AKA Super Mega Birthday Celebration at Yugo, a few kilometres away. Parents Tony and Lynn Forbes have released a joint statement confirming that he was shot dead. “It is with extreme sadness that we acknowledge the passing of our beloved son, and confirm his untimely and tragic passing. We are awaiting further details from the Durban police. To us, he was a son, brother, grandson, nephew, cousin and friend, most importantly father to his beloved daughter, Kairo,” read the statement. They added that to many people, he was affectionately known as AKA, Supermega and Bhova, among others. “Our son was loved and he gave love in return. In this time of grief, we appeal for your compassion, space and time to congregate as a family to decide on the upcoming days. We thank you for the love and support we have received thus far, and ask you to continue to keep us in your prayers and uplifted in the Lord.” OFFICIAL STATEMENT#RIPAKA pic.twitter.com/ajAL6pas7I  REGISTER TO COMMENT! It took about four hours for forensic workers and police to remove the bodies from the restaurant premises after being shot around 10pm. And, the police ensured that they were hidden from people. ALSO WATCH: Rapper AKA shot dead! An eyewitness, who did not want to be named, told Daily Sun that AKA and his friend were on their way out of the restaurant. “Everyone was shocked when they were shot by unknown gunmen. They fired shots and ran away. It was a sad day on Florida road as it is known for entertainment restaurants and bars.” Fans have been expressing their shock and conveying condolences on social media.